drinking beer, the person must

00:19:05.000 --> 00:19:06.590
be over 21?

00:19:06.590 --> 00:19:10.473
And you're told that you have
four items in front of you,

00:19:10.473 --> 00:19:14.890
and you're asked, which ones
do you need to turn over to

00:19:14.890 --> 00:19:16.370
verify the statement?

00:19:16.370 --> 00:19:18.998
So to verify the statement, if
there's an a on one side,

00:19:18.998 --> 00:19:21.300
there's a three on the other
side, you need to turn over

00:19:21.300 --> 00:19:24.390
the a and the seven, not
the a and the three.

00:19:24.390 --> 00:19:26.835
And that should become obvious
to you if you look at this

00:19:26.835 --> 00:19:30.365
case, where to determine
whether the person was

00:19:30.365 --> 00:19:33.890
drinking beer, the person must
be over 21, you need to turn

00:19:33.890 --> 00:19:38.760
over the card belonging to the
