00:19:43.400 --> 00:19:44.685
So does that clarify?

00:19:44.685 --> 00:19:45.990
Excellent.

00:19:45.990 --> 00:19:47.120
OK.

00:19:47.120 --> 00:19:52.670
So dual processing accounts
attempt to provide a general

00:19:52.670 --> 00:19:56.890
explanation for what's going
on in the cases I've just

00:19:56.890 --> 00:20:00.300
described, and in the cases
I'm about to describe.

00:20:00.300 --> 00:20:05.871
They suggest that we have two
relatively autonomous

00:20:05.871 --> 00:20:10.030
mechanisms for processing
information, and they're

00:20:10.030 --> 00:20:13.920
called all sorts of things,
but what's become the most

00:20:13.920 --> 00:20:18.010
normative way of describing
them, is to call them simply

00:20:18.010 --> 00:20:20.910
system one and system two.

00:20:20.910 --> 00:20:24.790
So whereas system one is
evolutionarily primitive--it

00:20:24.790 --> 00:20:28.935
makes use of parts of the
brain that came into our

00:20:28.935 --> 00:20:32.087
evolutionary process relatively
early in the

00:20:32.087 --> 00:20:36.440
game--system two is
evolutionarily relatively

00:20:36.440 --> 00:20:39.510
recent, it involves higher
cortical function.

00:20:39.510 --> 00:20:43.300
System one is unconscious, or
preconscious, whereas system

00:20:43.300 --> 00:20:45.174
two is conscious.

00:20:45.174 --> 00:20:49.340
System one operates
automatically, whereas system

00:20:49.340 --> 00:20:53.130
two is consciously controlled.

00:20:53.130 --> 00:20:56.611
System one is effortless, it
happens without our trying.

00:20:56.611 --> 00:21:00.734
System two is effortful, in the
sense that it involves an

00:21:00.734 --> 00:21:01.917
expenditure of cognitive
energy;

00:21:01.917 --> 00:21:04.390
you have to pay attention.

00:21:04.390 --> 00:21:08.970
System one is super fast. It
processes information almost

00:21:08.970 --> 00:21:10.490
instantaneously.

00:21:10.490 --> 00:21:12.680
System two is, relatively
speaking--

00:21:12.680 --> 00:21:15.900
slow, the information that we
get through system two takes

00:21:15.900 --> 00:21:19.384
considerably longer: seconds
rather than milliseconds.

00:21:19.384 --> 00:21:21.256
System one is associative.

00:21:21.256 --> 00:21:24.320
It recognizes patterns
in the world.

00:21:24.320 --> 00:21:26.170
System two is rule-based.

00:21:26.170 --> 00:21:28.700
It can apply principles.

00:21:28.700 --> 00:21:32.050
System one is, people sometimes
say, reflexive --

00:21:32.050 --> 00:21:36.435
it happens without reflection,
which is what

00:21:36.435 --> 00:21:40.420
underlies system two.

00:21:40.420 --> 00:21:46.066
So the distinction between
system one and system two is

00:21:46.066 --> 00:21:51.890
the result of many decades
of work by many people.

00:21:51.890 --> 00:21:55.600
Here's a chart from a different
paper by Jonathan

00:21:55.600 --> 00:21:57.655
Evans in which he enumerates--

00:21:57.655 --> 00:22:01.030
and this will be available
to you on the V2 site--

00:22:01.030 --> 00:22:06.220
some of the many researchers
whose work went into talking

00:22:06.220 --> 00:22:09.100
about system one
and system two.

00:22:09.100 --> 00:22:14.030
And I want to point out to you
one important thing here,

00:22:14.030 --> 00:22:17.486
which is that it's a bit
misleading to speak of system

00:22:17.486 --> 00:22:22.428
one and system two as if they
are individual things.

00:22:22.428 --> 00:22:26.990
System one is sometimes called
the autonomous set of

00:22:26.990 --> 00:22:31.120
subsystems. The idea: there is
the visual processing, and the

00:22:31.120 --> 00:22:33.355
auditory processing, and there's
processing that gives

00:22:33.355 --> 00:22:37.170
us very specific information
about things like faces, or

00:22:37.170 --> 00:22:40.220
the average length of lines,
or that enables us to

00:22:40.220 --> 00:22:43.280
recognize something as
predator or prey.

00:22:43.280 --> 00:22:46.722
All of those systems have
the characteristics

00:22:46.722 --> 00:22:48.130
that system one does.

00:22:48.130 --> 00:22:50.034
They're quick, they're
unconscious, they're

00:22:50.034 --> 00:22:52.690
evolutionarily primitive,
they come online without

00:22:52.690 --> 00:22:53.700
reflection.

00:22:53.700 --> 00:22:58.110
But they are not, each of them,
they are not altogether

00:22:58.110 --> 00:23:01.790
a coherent system.

00:23:01.790 --> 00:23:07.236
So dual processing accounts are
a way of trying to make

00:23:07.236 --> 00:23:11.907
sense of a set of phenomena,
some of which have to do with

00:23:11.907 --> 00:23:17.665
the processing of reasoning,
and some of which, as we

00:23:17.665 --> 00:23:22.420
learned in the absolutely lovely
Nobel Prize speech of

00:23:22.420 --> 00:23:26.605
Daniel Kahneman, which I asked
you to watch for today, some

00:23:26.605 --> 00:23:33.674
of which takes place in a more
general domain of reasoning.

00:23:33.674 --> 00:23:36.421
And I've reproduced for you
here Kahneman's beautiful

00:23:36.421 --> 00:23:39.805
chart explaining his
understanding of the relation

00:23:39.805 --> 00:23:42.060
between system one
and system two.

00:23:42.060 --> 00:23:45.606
Where he talks about the
similarities between

00:23:45.606 --> 00:23:48.860
perception and intuition
on the one hand and

00:23:48.860 --> 00:23:50.410
reasoning on the other.

00:23:50.410 --> 00:23:55.696
And again, I'll leave this slide
for you on the website.

