00:29:24.464 --> 00:29:27.507
Here's a study by Kahneman and
Tversky's student, Eldar

00:29:27.507 --> 00:29:30.440
Shafir, from the early 1990s.

00:29:30.440 --> 00:29:33.080
You go to an ice cream store,
and you're hoping to get

00:29:33.080 --> 00:29:35.340
yourself two flavors
of ice cream.

00:29:35.340 --> 00:29:39.630
One is a good flavor, the other
is an excellent flavor,

00:29:39.630 --> 00:29:42.010
but it has high cholesterol.

00:29:42.010 --> 00:29:46.882
And you discover that you only
have enough money to buy one

00:29:46.882 --> 00:29:48.806
of the ice creams.

00:29:48.806 --> 00:29:54.725
So if I asked you which one
would you choose, 28% of

00:29:54.725 --> 00:30:00.231
people choose the good flavor,
and 72% of people choose the

00:30:00.231 --> 00:30:03.920
excellent flavor with
high cholesterol.

00:30:03.920 --> 00:30:13.454
But if I ask you which one do
you give up, 55% of the people

00:30:13.454 --> 00:30:19.480
give up the one with the good
flavor, and 45% of the people

00:30:19.480 --> 00:30:24.552
give up the one with excellent
flavor, high cholesterol.

00:30:24.552 --> 00:30:28.564
So even though, in
this case, 28%--

00:30:28.564 --> 00:30:32.282
even though these are exactly
the same question, which do

00:30:32.282 --> 00:30:32.734
you choose?

00:30:32.734 --> 00:30:36.702
If you choose A, you give up B.
If you choose B, you give

00:30:36.702 --> 00:30:41.190
up A. These numbers
don't match up.

00:30:41.190 --> 00:30:45.100
When you're asked which one
you choose, the excellent

00:30:45.100 --> 00:30:50.130
looms large, and so you go for
it, neglecting the high

00:30:50.130 --> 00:30:51.090
cholesterol.

00:30:51.090 --> 00:30:53.895
When you're asked which one
you give up, the high

00:30:53.895 --> 00:30:55.720
cholesterol looms larger.

00:30:58.500 --> 00:31:01.740
This phenomenon occurs
over and over again.

00:31:01.740 --> 00:31:07.072
Suppose you're going to a movie,
and when you get to the

00:31:07.072 --> 00:31:10.540
theater, you discover that
you've lost something from

00:31:10.540 --> 00:31:12.370
your wallet.

00:31:12.370 --> 00:31:17.840
What you've lost from your
wallet is either a $10 bill or

00:31:17.840 --> 00:31:21.602
a $10 movie ticket which
you had purchased last

00:31:21.602 --> 00:31:23.924
night for the movie.

00:31:23.924 --> 00:31:27.100
You get to the theater, you
open your wallet to go in,

00:31:27.100 --> 00:31:29.860
either, in the first case, to
pull out a $10 bill to buy the

00:31:29.860 --> 00:31:33.600
ticket, or in the second case,
to pull out your "Admit 1"

00:31:33.600 --> 00:31:36.960
ticket to let yourself in, and
you discover that you've lost

00:31:36.960 --> 00:31:39.328
the item that would have
enabled you to

00:31:39.328 --> 00:31:42.256
get into the theater.

00:31:42.256 --> 00:31:46.160
However, you have another $10
bill in your pocket, and the

00:31:46.160 --> 00:31:53.005
question is: do you buy
another movie ticket?

