as a $10 bill, only 42% said
that they would spend the $10

00:32:14.050 --> 00:32:15.660
to buy another ticket.

00:32:18.985 --> 00:32:24.890
So framing is one of the
examples of a heuristic, or

00:32:24.890 --> 00:32:26.966
bias, which Kahneman
and Tversky

00:32:26.966 --> 00:32:30.622
focus on in their work.

00:32:30.622 --> 00:32:34.952
We will return to some other
examples later in the

00:32:34.952 --> 00:32:38.062
semester, when we read the
work of Cass Sunstein.

00:32:38.062 --> 00:32:41.400
What I want to point you to now
is a particular example,

00:32:41.400 --> 00:32:45.750
which is going to serve as our
segue into the idea of alief.

00:32:45.750 --> 00:32:48.380
And that's the distinction
between frequency and

00:32:48.380 --> 00:32:49.751
probability.

00:32:49.751 --> 00:32:53.713
So suppose you're trying to get
a red ball because getting

00:32:53.713 --> 00:32:57.014
a red ball will help
you win a prize.

00:32:57.014 --> 00:33:02.250
And you have a choice about
whether you want to draw from

00:33:02.250 --> 00:33:06.732
this box over here, which has
nine white balls and one red

00:33:06.732 --> 00:33:14.235
one, or this box over here,
which has eight red balls and

00:33:14.235 --> 00:33:16.002
92 white ones.

00:33:16.002 --> 00:33:20.560
So here you have a 10% chance,
here you have an 8% chance.

00:33:20.560 --> 00:33:25.270
And you're going to be drawing
from the boxes blindfolded.

00:33:25.270 --> 00:33:28.710
An image for which I don't
suggest doing Google search.

00:33:32.561 --> 00:33:33.250
So, I found blindfolded
justice.

00:33:33.250 --> 00:33:34.500
That did a little better.

00:33:36.830 --> 00:33:37.744
All right.

00:33:37.744 --> 00:33:39.580
So you have your choice.

00:33:39.580 --> 00:33:42.174
Do you want to let this
box be the one --

00:33:42.174 --> 00:33:44.260
you're trying to get a red ball,
-- do you want to let

00:33:44.260 --> 00:33:46.650
this box be the one, or
do you want to let

00:33:46.650 --> 00:33:48.550
this box be the one?

00:33:48.550 --> 00:33:53.571
Obviously, rationally, you've
got a better chance over here.

00:33:53.571 --> 00:33:59.525
But people are in fact pulled
in two directions.

00:33:59.525 --> 00:34:03.324
You had a 10% chance over here,
but my goodness, there's

00:34:03.324 --> 00:34:05.080
8 balls over here!

00:34:05.080 --> 00:34:05.960
8 8!

00:34:05.960 --> 00:34:06.840
1 8!

00:34:06.840 --> 00:34:07.720
1 8!

00:34:07.720 --> 00:34:08.130
More!

00:34:08.130 --> 00:34:08.540
More!

00:34:08.540 --> 00:34:10.484
More!

00:34:10.484 --> 00:34:14.785
What's going on here, I suggest,
is that whereas you

00:34:14.785 --> 00:34:20.889
have a belief that here, you
have 10% chance, you have what

00:34:20.889 --> 00:34:26.058
I call an alief that here there
are eight, whereas over

00:34:26.058 --> 00:34:29.335
there, there is one.

00:34:29.335 --> 00:34:36.140
So alief is a notion that I've
actually discussed on

00:34:36.140 --> 00:34:41.840
bloggingheads.tv with
Paul Bloom.

00:34:41.840 --> 00:34:45.823
And though we were filming in
different places, here I am in

00:34:45.823 --> 00:34:48.836
the game room at my house with
our geo-puzzles, here's Paul

00:34:48.836 --> 00:34:53.180
in the study, it appears that
we were separated at birth,

00:34:53.180 --> 00:35:00.640
because that's at the same
time as that photo.

00:35:00.640 --> 00:35:02.550
All right.

00:35:02.550 --> 00:35:07.696
So suppose I take you to the
Grand Canyon, and I bring you

00:35:07.696 --> 00:35:12.036
out on the glass walkway that
extends 4,000 feet above the

00:35:12.036 --> 00:35:13.920
roaring river below.

00:35:13.920 --> 00:35:16.875
And you step out there
with me, and you

00:35:16.875 --> 00:35:20.022
voluntarily remain there.

00:35:20.022 --> 00:35:23.524
I take it if you voluntarily
remain on a glass surface

00:35:23.524 --> 00:35:27.270
4,000 feet above a roaring
river, you believe that

00:35:27.270 --> 00:35:29.926
surface is safe.

00:35:29.926 --> 00:35:34.950
Nonetheless, I will wager that
most of you would shudder and

00:35:34.950 --> 00:35:37.060
shiver and shake.

00:35:37.060 --> 00:35:41.568
And you'd do so because you
have what I would call an

00:35:41.568 --> 00:35:46.230
alief that says to you, "I am
4,000 feet in the air, with

00:35:46.230 --> 00:35:51.110
nothing holding me here, and
I'm going to tremble."

00:35:51.110 --> 00:35:53.980
Or suppose we're watching a
Western movie -- anybody

00:35:53.980 --> 00:35:59.205
recognize that gentleman
who was president

00:35:59.205 --> 00:36:02.015
when you were born?

00:36:02.015 --> 00:36:05.106
When you watch a movie, a
Western movie, and the bullets

00:36:05.106 --> 00:36:07.572
are flying off the stage,
obviously you believe that

00:36:07.572 --> 00:36:08.410
you're safe.

00:36:08.410 --> 00:36:12.136
You don't think, "oh, what a
good thing it was that the

00:36:12.136 --> 00:36:14.900
bullets didn't come off
the screen this time".

00:36:14.900 --> 00:36:20.770
Nonetheless, particularly
in 3D, you will

00:36:20.770 --> 00:36:22.333
bend your head down.

00:36:22.333 --> 00:36:24.780
If the green slime is coming off
the screen, you'll tremble

00:36:24.780 --> 00:36:25.430
in your seat.

00:36:25.430 --> 00:36:27.794
If Anna Karenina is about
to die, you will cry.

00:36:27.794 --> 00:36:31.686
Not because you believe that
you're in danger, but because

00:36:31.686 --> 00:36:33.700
you have an alief.

00:36:33.700 --> 00:36:37.660
How many of you set your watch
five minutes fast, and then

00:36:37.660 --> 00:36:40.136
subtract back down?

00:36:40.136 --> 00:36:42.232
When you do it, you believe
that it's ten

00:36:42.232 --> 00:36:43.840
but you have an alief--

00:36:43.840 --> 00:36:45.370
you look down at it --

00:36:45.370 --> 00:36:45.720
10:05!

00:36:45.720 --> 00:36:46.775
It enters your visual system ,
it gets processed really fast

00:36:46.775 --> 00:36:49.840
and it says "10:05!

00:36:49.840 --> 00:36:51.704
Hurry!"

00:36:51.704 --> 00:36:56.524
Or suppose you're watching a
rerun of your favorite team on

00:36:56.524 --> 00:37:01.575
television, and you know that if
one of the guys on the team

00:37:01.575 --> 00:37:05.560
tries to steal second, he's
going to be thrown out.

00:37:05.560 --> 00:37:09.868
And so you yell at the
television screen, "Don't run!

00:37:09.868 --> 00:37:11.780
Don't run!" Why?

00:37:11.780 --> 00:37:14.348
Because you believe that your
voice is going to go through

00:37:14.348 --> 00:37:20.540
the television screen, back in
time, to first base to reach

00:37:20.540 --> 00:37:21.280
the runner?

00:37:21.280 --> 00:37:21.700
No.

00:37:21.700 --> 00:37:25.095
You have a belief that it's a
rerun, and your alief says

00:37:25.095 --> 00:37:26.656
"don't run".

00:37:26.656 --> 00:37:29.458
Suppose you're on a diet, and
you see this beautiful piece

00:37:29.458 --> 00:37:32.254
of chocolate cake and you have
the belief that it's

00:37:32.254 --> 00:37:33.990
undesirable.

00:37:33.990 --> 00:37:38.376
Your alief system, in the form
of your Platonic horse may

00:37:38.376 --> 00:37:40.900
nonetheless pull
you towards it.

00:37:40.900 --> 00:37:46.228
Suppose I present you with this
delicious cake, those are

00:37:46.228 --> 00:37:50.650
Tootsie rolls, this is a
perfectly clean and sterilized

00:37:50.650 --> 00:37:54.252
pan, that's coconut there, in
fact, this one has the same

00:37:54.252 --> 00:37:57.766
ingredients as that
one, exactly.

00:37:57.766 --> 00:37:59.230
You believe me, right?

00:37:59.230 --> 00:38:01.059
I'm your professor, you're
here, listening

00:38:01.059 --> 00:38:01.725
to what I tell you.

00:38:01.725 --> 00:38:03.222
I tell you, this is edible!

00:38:03.222 --> 00:38:05.218
Tootsie rolls, coconut.

00:38:05.218 --> 00:38:07.214
Nonetheless, I take
it that your alief

00:38:07.214 --> 00:38:09.910
system kicks into gear.

00:38:09.910 --> 00:38:13.570
Suppose I ask you to sign this
contract: "I hereby assert

00:38:13.570 --> 00:38:16.810
that my soul belongs only
to you, O Satan".

00:38:16.810 --> 00:38:20.470
And I write at the bottom, "This
is not a legal contract.

00:38:20.470 --> 00:38:25.520
It's just a prompt in a
psychology experiment." You

00:38:25.520 --> 00:38:27.694
will, nonetheless, be reluctant
to sign, not because

00:38:27.694 --> 00:38:30.990
you don't believe that this is
a legal contract, right?

00:38:30.990 --> 00:38:31.239
[high-piched voice]

00:38:31.239 --> 00:38:34.103
"Oh my goodness, if I sign my
soul over to the devil, I can

00:38:34.103 --> 00:38:39.390
tell it's the devil--it's
parchment." No.

00:38:39.390 --> 00:38:42.757
You believe that there's
nothing to it, but

00:38:42.757 --> 00:38:44.320
nonetheless, you hesitate.

00:38:44.320 --> 00:38:49.660
Suppose I take you to Monica
Bonvicini's bathroom, which

00:38:49.660 --> 00:38:54.202
is, as you can see, completely
opaque from the outside.

00:38:54.202 --> 00:38:57.400
You stand outside this public
restroom, you peer into it,

00:38:57.400 --> 00:39:00.660
you see that there's no
way to see inside.

00:39:00.660 --> 00:39:03.542
You belief is that you are
totally protected.

00:39:03.542 --> 00:39:08.170
Nonetheless, when you go in
to use the facilities,

00:39:08.170 --> 00:39:10.100
it looks like that.

00:39:10.100 --> 00:39:16.467
And your alief makes it rather
difficult to do what you had

00:39:16.467 --> 00:39:21.440
gone in with the intention
of doing.

00:39:21.440 --> 00:39:27.997
Suppose we have a bag of sugar
and two glasses of water.

00:39:27.997 --> 00:39:32.578
And you take a spoonful of the
sugar, and you put one in this

00:39:32.578 --> 00:39:36.208
glass and label it "Sugar,"
and one in this glass and

00:39:36.208 --> 00:39:41.660
label it "Poison." You took the
sugar, you put it in the

00:39:41.660 --> 00:39:44.770
glasses, you put the
labels on it.

00:39:44.770 --> 00:39:48.174
Nonetheless, people
are reluctant to

00:39:48.174 --> 00:39:50.214
drink from this glass.

00:39:50.214 --> 00:39:52.630
Moreover, they're not just
reluctant to drink from it

00:39:52.630 --> 00:39:53.940
when it says poison.

00:39:53.940 --> 00:39:56.719
They're reluctant to drink from
it when they've written

00:39:56.719 --> 00:39:59.312
the words Not Poison on it.

00:39:59.312 --> 00:39:59.805
Why?

00:39:59.805 --> 00:40:01.284
Because the word poison
is there.

00:40:01.284 --> 00:40:04.100
Running into your
alief system.

00:40:04.100 --> 00:40:04.670
Good sugar.

00:40:04.670 --> 00:40:07.140
Mmm drink sugar.

00:40:07.140 --> 00:40:07.355
Poison?

00:40:07.355 --> 00:40:08.000
Poison?

00:40:08.000 --> 00:40:09.933
Don't drink the poison!

00:40:09.933 --> 00:40:11.322
--OK.

00:40:11.322 --> 00:40:17.318
Suppose that I have a kitchen,
and I'm interested in making

00:40:17.318 --> 00:40:19.615
some kitty litter cake,
so I have my cake

00:40:19.615 --> 00:40:22.073
pans stored over here.

00:40:22.073 --> 00:40:26.000
And a chef comes in and says to
me, it would be much more

00:40:26.000 --> 00:40:30.420
efficient if the cake pan
were over on the right.

00:40:30.420 --> 00:40:33.230
He's very pleased with
what he's done.

00:40:33.230 --> 00:40:37.640
And when I ask him to get the
cake pan, he says, "I'm so

00:40:37.640 --> 00:40:40.265
happy that we moved the
muffin tin cake

00:40:40.265 --> 00:40:41.930
to the right cabinet".

00:40:41.930 --> 00:40:45.540
And those two get it, believing
it could be on the

00:40:45.540 --> 00:40:49.470
right, exactly where
it used to be.

00:40:49.470 --> 00:40:52.550
His belief is that it's
on the right.

00:40:52.550 --> 00:40:57.180
His alief is a lagging habit.

00:40:57.180 --> 00:41:00.357
Any of you who has ever
rearranged your room knows

00:41:00.357 --> 00:41:01.010
this feeling.

00:41:01.010 --> 00:41:04.778
Any of you who has ever put your
cell phone in your hand,

00:41:04.778 --> 00:41:06.796
and then looked for
your cell phone--

00:41:06.796 --> 00:41:09.524
I've had terrors of having lost
my children, and then

00:41:09.524 --> 00:41:10.856
realized they were
on my shoulder.

00:41:14.326 --> 00:41:19.180
So to have an alief is roughly
to have a representationally

00:41:19.180 --> 00:41:24.693
mediated propensity to respond
to an apparent stimulus in a

00:41:24.693 --> 00:41:25.635
particular way.

00:41:25.635 --> 00:41:26.106
Right?

00:41:26.106 --> 00:41:28.990
So the apparent stimulus of
the glass staircase, the

00:41:28.990 --> 00:41:32.860
apparent stimulus of the kitty
litter cake, you have a

00:41:32.860 --> 00:41:36.938
propensity, that's either
innate, as in the case of the

00:41:36.938 --> 00:41:44.145
glass, or the fudge shaped
like feces, or a habitual

00:41:44.145 --> 00:41:47.855
propensity, as when you
arrange the kitchen.

00:41:47.855 --> 00:41:53.540
These are habitual ways of
responding to the world that

00:41:53.540 --> 00:41:56.030
activate the sort of lower-level
systems that we've

00:41:56.030 --> 00:41:57.670
been talking about.

00:41:57.670 --> 00:42:01.020
And importantly--although we
can recognize alief most

00:42:01.020 --> 00:42:04.606
easily by looking at these kinds
of discordant cases, the

00:42:04.606 --> 00:42:08.230
cases where belief tells you
to do one thing, and alief

00:42:08.230 --> 00:42:09.815
tells you to do the other.

00:42:09.815 --> 00:42:15.050
In fact, alief is active
all the time.

00:42:15.050 --> 00:42:19.740
Every time I've used my right
thumb to push the key on this,

00:42:19.740 --> 00:42:22.420
I've done it out of alief.

00:42:22.420 --> 00:42:25.920
Fortunately, it's one that
corresponds with what I intend

00:42:25.920 --> 00:42:30.986
to do, but it is certainly
the case that an enormous

00:42:30.986 --> 00:42:36.668
proportion of our actions
are governed by alief.

00:42:36.668 --> 00:42:38.917
The question is this.

00:42:38.917 --> 00:42:43.370
Given that I just showed you
that there are hundreds and

00:42:43.370 --> 00:42:48.078
hundreds of ways of describing
what I adverted to with the

00:42:48.078 --> 00:42:54.050
notion of alief, why introduce
this new term?

00:42:57.412 --> 00:43:02.260
The story has something to
do with alief itself.

00:43:02.260 --> 00:43:07.850
So every 20 years or so, the
United States government

00:43:07.850 --> 00:43:09.320
introduces a dollar coin.

00:43:09.320 --> 00:43:12.870
Here's the one they introduced
in 1921.

00:43:12.870 --> 00:43:16.253
Here's the one they introduced
in 1972.

00:43:16.253 --> 00:43:20.940
Here's the one they introduced
later in the 1980s.

00:43:20.940 --> 00:43:22.965
Here's the one they introduced
in 1980,

00:43:22.965 --> 00:43:24.551
with Susan B. Anthony.

00:43:24.551 --> 00:43:29.160
Here's the Sacajawea one they
introduced in 2003, and in a

00:43:29.160 --> 00:43:32.840
massive fit of public relations
genius, here's the

00:43:32.840 --> 00:43:38.410
Millard Fillmore golden coin,
which will be issued soon.

00:43:38.410 --> 00:43:40.400
What's going on here?

00:43:40.400 --> 00:43:44.340
What's going on here is that
it's hard to get people to

00:43:44.340 --> 00:43:49.190
make use of something if it
doesn't fit into the currency

00:43:49.190 --> 00:43:53.250
system which they
have already.

00:43:53.250 --> 00:43:57.730
Dollar coins don't fit naturally
into the ways that

00:43:57.730 --> 00:44:02.260
Americans use money.

00:44:02.260 --> 00:44:07.135
Likewise, talk of system one,
system two, relatively

00:44:07.135 --> 00:44:12.485
autonomous systems, heuristics
biases and so on, don't fit

00:44:12.485 --> 00:44:16.290
naturally into the way
that we have of

00:44:16.290 --> 00:44:18.486
talking about ourselves.

00:44:18.486 --> 00:44:23.260
We talk about ourselves in terms
of beliefs and desires.

00:44:23.260 --> 00:44:29.680
And in order to make use of
the gold coin that is the

00:44:29.680 --> 00:44:34.320
recognition of the multipartite
soul, we need a

00:44:34.320 --> 00:44:38.280
notion that fits into our
conceptual currency.

00:44:38.280 --> 00:44:44.280
And that's the role that my
hope is alief will play.

00:44:44.280 --> 00:44:48.364
So alief is going to return
to us in later lectures.

00:44:48.364 --> 00:44:51.598
We'll hear about it again in the
context of the harmony of

00:44:51.598 --> 00:44:54.760
the soul and in other domains,
we'll hear about heuristic and

00:44:54.760 --> 00:44:58.630
biases and we'll hear about
the multipart soul.

00:44:58.630 --> 00:45:01.483
I look forward to seeing all of
you on Tuesday for harmony

00:45:01.483 --> 00:45:02.733
and happiness.

